/a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The height of an ideal is defined as the infimum of the heights of its minimal prime ideals. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Height.html#Ideal.height","kind":"def","line":39,"name":"Ideal.height","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Height.lean#L39-L41"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Height.html#Ideal.primeHeight\"><span class=\"name\">Ideal</span>.<span class=\"name\">primeHeight</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">I</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Defs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">hI</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">I</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Prime.html#Ideal.IsPrime\">IsPrime</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENat/Defs.html#ENat\">ℕ∞</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The height of a prime ideal is defined as the supremum of the lengths of strictly decreasing\nchains of prime ideals below it. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Height.html#Ideal.primeHeight","kind":"def","line":34,"name":"Ideal.primeHeight","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib